				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In NTSC interlaced video, there are "odd fields" and there are "even fields", depending on where the synchronization pulses fall at the start of the vertical blanking period prior to the frame. One of the field types is drawn half a scanline down, and a signal that alternates odd and even fields produces a 480i display. But if a video signal is all odd fields or all even fields, most TVs will interpret it as a 240p signal.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

